<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This is a pretty outrageous example of Verant's lackluster customer service.<P>In ANY kind of business, the company is usually required to show respect towards their customers.  This usually involves taking steps to warn the customer that he/she/they are abusing the service, and to cease.  (Unless, of course, the abuse is extreme, such as hooking up a black box to your TV, or, an EQ example, using the /shout channel to promote your new Third Reich.)  If the violator fails to comply, it is then considered just and fair to suspend their service.  If you miss a payment to the cable company, they don't suspend your service right away.  They send you several dire letters in the mail, and when those go unanswered, cut the service.<P>Verant has completely circumvented this.  It appears these players were never warned.  Just *gank* and off goes EQ.  Yes, they were violating the Terms of Service.<P>However, that particular passage in the ToS is kind of silly.  It states that you will not exploit any of our mistakes.  I'm currently working towards my degree in computer science.  It is the responsibility of the programmer to make sure his product works, not the consumer's job to be careful they are doing things as they were intended.<P>Now I understand that due to the nature of EQ and that it is a continuously changing game, this cannot always be done.  However, people at VI should know by now that when someone breaks into a zone the magnitude of Sleeper's Tomb, it will be all over ever EQ website in existance.  Anything that happens there, a bestiary, lots of screenshots, everything.  You would want to make sure it was PERFECT.  That way, the company would look good.<P>Instead, Verant blames the player, for noticing and utilizing their mistakes.  It's not your user's fault; we've all heard the saying that works surprisingly well in business- "The customer is always right."  Shady, shady business practices by VI.    <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"> <P>Claud Shadowflare<BR>45 Wizard of Xegony
</FONT>
