Well, if CQ did everything that Verant said, then CQ was in the wrong.  But, if players cannot use exploits using game geometry, hate-list, z-coordinate, etc, neither should mobs.  Running through a wall, being beneath the ground, aggroing through a wall, etc. should be eliminated.  I helped a druid friend kill Ulump in Swamp of No Hope, and Ulump ran into the water from where we pulled on the maruader island, and regened to 1/2 health in 1 second.  He did this twice, before killing us.  We ended up killing him at his spawn point.<P>I hear talk of "engine cant do this" or "game engine cannot do that"......well, I frankly don't care.  Its a problem in the game, its VI's responsibility to fix it, regardless of the issue or problem.  I didn't pay for the game and $10 a month for a buggy game.  Either they fix it, or revise the in-game customer service where if the game does mess up, the player doesn't have to wait 2 hours for a GM to show up to fix it.  I'm not upset at "most" GMs, they do what they can, according to guidelines set by VI.<P>Frankly, I am a typcial customer.  I don't want excuses on how the engine cant do this or that would take too long, I want results and solutions to problems.<P>A slightly disgruntled player.
