" The customer is Always right" .... Ha what a bunch of hogwash.<P>The fact is the customer is generally wrong. The customer has no idea how a perticular company creates, distributes, updates, or markets their product. The only get the end result. Of course if the company produces a flawed product and it is purchased by a customer what can he/she do? .... Return it and get a refund obviously. Of course even to do that you must follow their rules on returning the product. If you wait to long, lose the reciept, or purposely damage the product you can be eaisly turned down for the refund. While getting pissy or encountering a generous salesman can help.<P>The fact is VI posted their rules and it seems at least according to VI the guild broke them. Obviously, if someone breaks them and gets caught how many of us generelly say, yep you caught me, no no no. Its not in our nature. We do our best to hide this fact from others who do not know what exactly happened. After all its one word against the other.<P><BR>Should they be banned? .. You betch ya.<P>Cheating in many FPS games has gotten waaaaaayyy out of hand and fortunately some are trying to do something about it. CAL for instance just banned and removed a promminent CS clan for cheating. The same goes here. Different games : same rules<P><BR>Remember if your going to break them. Don't get caught and certainly don't brag about it.
