<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
One of the biggest arguements that you will see supporting the guild is that its all Verants fault for having exploitable bugs in their game. People who use this argument ignore two things. <BR>1) There is no software package of this size used by this many people updated this often that is completely bug/exploit free.<BR>2) People who use these exploits and specifically know they are exploits are responsible for their own actions when they are caught violating the TOS.<P>Other arguments in the support of the guild will be along the lines of the last US president...."it depends on what the meaning of exploit is". Its pretty obvious that trying to hide Clerics from agro using the z-axis and water involves "bugs that grant the user unnatural or unintended benefits in game".<P>The guild and guild leader may have been creative in devising a strategy to defeat the 4th warder but that doesn't hold them harmless from using strategies that include exploits. <P>As to the question of the punishment for using the exploit some may deem it too harsh. Perhaps so, but I don't think we can fully determine that without seeing the full logs and knowing their past history. Only Verant and the guild have access to that info.<P>Kelset<BR>Sol Ro
