All i can really say is that i think Verant went about this in the entirely wrong way. I didn't even KNOW there was a bug in summoning and i have been playing this game for awhile and been summoned i don't know how many times (nobody likes us druids). And it is basic tactics to keep your clerics away from the mob as much as possible, so the clerics not being in range of something during a fight is NOT unusual. And there should have been a warning of some kind, not an announcement that "you are exploiting stop fighting in the middle of the hardest dungeon in the game" the least that the GM's could have done is go in there and tell the entire guild to stop first of all and then explain why they should stop instead of just going and disbanding an entire guild. Now, i know GM's aren't always at fault for what they have to do, i mean its their job and they have to follow the rules, but they might have thought more about what to do instead of suspending/banning players right off the bat and disbanding the entire guild.<P>--------------------<P>Forestwolf Silvereyes<BR>50 Druid of Mithaniel Marr
