Ok, I'm gonna try my best to write this in a way such that the castersrealm guys won't have to delete it.. I may not be successful.<P>Verant, very seriously, are the most irresponsible, hardlined, hypocritical people in the world.  They Ban for *nothing* if they feel like it.  Let me tell you my story, and this is 100% true.  I swear it is, even tho nobody on the Eq official boards believed me when I posted this there before Verant (predictably) nazified the boards.<P>I have been in Eq since beta.  I've paid and played with ZERO warnings for well over 200 DAYS of gametime.  Thats over 4000 HOURS spent trying to get the most out of my ten bucks in their wretched product.  I submitted 2 dupe bugs, one of which was *definitely* the first report of it yet I never even got a thank you.  I submitted a bug on how to summon and *use* an infinite amount of pets.  I submitted how to SOLO Nagafen *yes, in this instance it was an exploit, tho I never actually killed nagafen figuring this out.. only took him down to the "N", I had no dragon loot, and I reported it, I had GM's crawling all over Nagafen as I showed them how to do it*  This bug STILL works (confirmed it with one of my other accounts, you just have to be a pet caster, yes, I DID kill the dragon this time, don't care anymore)  I won't tell you how to do it here since castersrealm would be forced to delete this post.<BR>I have consistantly reported every bug I have found throughout my everquest career. (up until I got banned)  <BR>One day, I read a report on how Verant used their limitless legal reserves to intimidate and threaten a small, independantly owned auction site, after they shut Ebay auctions of EQ stuff down.  I recognize that Verant may have had a case, tho I don't think so.  The point is that Site didn't even have a chance to state their case in court.  They were forced to shut down completely or lose all of their computer equipment and spend the night in Jail.  Verant was able to do this because they have a whole lot of money.  This *really* pissed me off.  I got on the official Verant gameplay forum and posted on why I thought this sucked bad.  I made a HUGE mistake tho.  I was pretty pissed and I didn't know how big of a freak Verant was willing to be so I wrote, "Verant Sux".  Irresponsible, yes, not quite appropriate.  The next day I was BANNED.  No warnings, no lecture, nothing, I was Banned.  You know whats worse tho?  They kept six months worth of Dues that I had paid in advance, no refund, even tho I asked for it back.  I made one *very* minor error such as saying the almight and omnipotent verant Sux.  In return they completely negated the 4000 hours I had put into their stupid game.  I'm going to include the emails I received from Verant when I complained at the bottom of this letter.  My character was lvl 55, with no dragon gear, no uber gear at all so you know I wasn't exploiting anything I found and in fact one of the emails from Verant says straight out that there were no "warnings" at issue. I am still considering filling an official theft complaint with my local prosecutor in regards to the $60 that they *stole* from me.<BR> <BR>What did this accomplish for Verant?  Nothing... nothing at all.  I now can't stand them.  The second that Vroutfitters.com opens for business I will be getting on Everquest, farming everything that I can, using every single cheat that I can, including ones in Kael, Velketors, and Chardok in order to sell items and make back that 60 dollars back a thousand fold.  <P>My real point here is this.  Verant Bans so easily, so arbitrarily that nobodys account is safe, no matter how "good" a player you think you are.  If you paid $60, and then found one of the uncountable bugs THAT HAVE PROBABLY BEEN REPORTED AND LEFT INGAME, got banned for it straight out simply because some GM can't feel powerful enough in the REAL world, wouldn't you feel that you deserved *at least* your 60 bucks back?<P>These guys in Conquest may have been cheating, it obviously can be done, even on super creatures like Nagafen, but getting banned for it straight out is ridiculous after the amount of money and time these guys have been putting into the game, considering that those bugs they are getting banned for have been created by Verant themselves due to their sloppy work.  Several of those hours have been nothing more than PAYING TO TEST verants own product, I guarantee it.<P>One way or the other, I'll be the guy selling the Sarnak Battle shield for pennies on the dollar.
