I think Verant did the right thing.<P>Why?<P>Well you folks only tend to see the "Well we are customers" side.<BR>But we are also people in RL that wanted to be protected by the police arent we?<BR>So if anyone in RL "exploits" a gun to shoot an innocent person do you think the police should warn them before shooting back, maybe risking another life?<P>Conquest was FULLY AWARE that they were exploiting big time. The Z-Axis summon bug is well know and can be exploited in other dungeons, I personally know a person that was banned for it and after that he feels he totally deserved it.<BR>In not so hard ways you get warned by VI Customer Service anytime. I was myself once exploiting a minor bug (wont say which) and was warned by a Guide that this may have actions against my account. But in a big situation like this (I mean Sleepers isnt cake is it?) I think they did the right thing. A place like this should be taken down the first time by people who deserve whatever fat loot the 4th warder gives, by taking him out with good strategies and cool people without exploiting any bugs. Same goes for the sleeper.<P>I know I will get flamed for this, but I want to play this game in a honorable way. Once I thought Gorenaire was undoable and we took it out without exploiting. Once I thought Nexonia was undoable, we took it out without exploiting. Same will happen with the 4th warder, he seems undoable, but time will show us a way, without exploiting!
