Since (technically) the above post conveys a "bug" (at least by their definition) I'll repost it here in case CastersRealm has to remove the above one. (And yes, that "feature" has been reported.)<BR>---------------------------------------------<BR>Being a Lead Engineer for another product and a player, I see both sides.<BR>1) You can't allow the players to PL TOO much, or the game's worthless.<BR>2) You can't fix everything.<BR>3) It's never "perfect."<P>They used z-axis geometry to keep from being hit? Bah, how many spell casters have NOT tried that? It's common sense. It's NOT common sense to have the mobs teleport ~15 storys STRAIGHT UP or be able to have "unlimited HtH attack range" in the z-axis. In fact, I filed a bug report on it.<BR>Exploitable? Yes - by the game.<P>Manipulating the hate-list? Again, how many people have NOT? "Oh look, the cleric's being hit, I'd better get it's attention!<BR>Wait, doh, I can't manipulate the hate-list to save the cleric...I'll wait 'till he's dead."<P>Bad pathing - okay, that one's fuzzy, but it's not a "common sense" thing, so leave it as a bug. Outsmarting a mob, yes, but it's a limitation of current technology.<P>Water/land combat? I had a Firona Drixie chase my arse down the other night. It's a FLYING INSECT. How can it swim? And has it practised swimming? It beat my swimming skill of 110! Exploitable? Yes - by the game. Did you know that piranha's can attack OUT of the water, but that YOU can't attack across the water boundry, even via spells/archery?<P>Verant built the world, the engine, the creatures, and, in fact, BUILT THE PHYSICS engine. Sure, you do have to draw the line somewhere...but if people have reported z-axis problems (and I know for a fact that they have) then perhaps you should consider fixing them? Maybe?<P>In FoB (Kunark) I can reproduce the "invisible mob" syndrome in which an undetectable mob can hit you, but you cannot hit back. It is invisible to every known "sight" spell. The only way to live is