<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Those guys got banned and rightly so.  Here's the most simple reason why:<P>They KNEW what they were doing was wrong.  <P>Unless Verant just made up the quote in their official statement or falsified the stuff (unlikely, no motive besides lame conspiracy theories about a zone/storyline being unfinished/unready).<P>I could easily understand outrage at a guild being disbanded/banned over taking actions which ppl are now saying are in the "grey."  But to be sitting there telling your guild its an exploit and saying you're in trouble if a GM sees it?  Give me a break.  People, don't let your own bad experiences with Verant (which may be quite legitimate) steer you away from this guild's conscious decision to do the WRONG thing.  If you believe that Verant is in some way making this stuff up, then I have no response to that as I have no firsthand knowledge.  I DO however know that it makes no sound business sense to upset a decent portion of the playerbase (as they have done) unless an actual incident has occurred.<P>Finally, as for them standing around watching the people exploit.  Well, that's a bit of entrapment-type behavior going on there I would agree.  On the other hand, the blatantly conscious nature of this guild's misdeed outweighs this argument.  They KNEW they were doing wrong.  If the GM's would have informed them, is this really telling the guild of a "grey" area?  No, they already know!  It would stop the guild only because they would be sure they'd be caught. <P>Anyway, there's alot of things Verant does which upsets me, including their shabby coding.  But CONSCIOUS exploiters upset me just as much.  That's weak and should be punished.  It's not "clever" in the least.  They weren't saying "oooh the GM's would be so impressed if they saw us using our clever method."  They said we're SOL if we get caught doing this.  Not clever.  And they got caught.   I don't think the policy for conscious misbehavior such as this should be altered at all.
