Seems that someone at Verant overreacted.<P>If they were indeed observing this blatant exploitation, then the "encounter" should have been stopped right then and there.<P>Warnings should have been issued, the groups summoned to a neutral area, and make them break in again (minus drops).<P>That *IS*, providing they were truly guilty. Yes, Verant can pull the guild chat logs, I'm sure. But I'm also sure, just as Conquest did on their behalf, Verant slanted those statements to be the most condemning possible.<P>Maybe both sides were in the wrong. We have to play by their rules. But is it a fault that the players often are a step ahead in creativity, understanding of how the game works, and implementation of such strategies?<P>Not condoning use of exploits, but how many times have items or abilities been (ugh, sorry) *nerfed* after we found ways to maximize them beyond what Verant had envisioned? Clerics alone will testify to that.<P>A warning should have been issued. Verant needs to hire more testers. Whatever the case, this was handled poorly.<P>Three sides to every story...Yours, Theirs, and the Truth.<P>Karkas, 52 DE Heretic<BR>Quellious
